      <p>
        Over the last four years I&rsquo;ve shipped LLM systems in finance, e-commerce, and
        regulated compliance. I build directly against provider SDKs rather than through
        frameworks, because the parts that matter (prompts, data, evals, latency) are the
        parts frameworks don&rsquo;t help with.
      </p>
      <p>
        Right now I&rsquo;m a <strong>KTP Associate at Pimberly &times; University of Essex</strong>,
        building an EU compliance platform that produces Digital Product Passports.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before that, I led the AI team at <strong>Elixir</strong> that shipped a RAG financial
        chatbot on WhatsApp, and migrated a negotiation chatbot at <strong>Nibble</strong>
        from rule-based NLU to LLM-driven generation. My first IEEE paper, on MicroVM
        honeypot isolation, is out at CSR 2026.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the side, I take on a small number of <strong>consultancy engagements</strong>:
        audits, prototypes, and full builds for teams who want production-ready AI without
        the framework sprawl. Happy to talk through specifics on a short intro call.
      </p>
